The FCT police command’s Anti-Narcotic Unit has burst five drug syndicates at Gwarinpa, Galadimawa, Karu and Apo, all Abuja suburbs. A statement by the spokesman of the command, DSP Anjuguri Manzah, said some suspects were arrested during the special operation carried out by the unit, which he said led to recovery of 14 wraps of cocaine, 292 wraps of dried leaves suspected to be Indian hemp and other hard drugs. He said the suspects arrested during the operations were Anas Abubakar,  Musa Buhari, Abdullahi Adamu, Mahi Ibrahim, Sanusi Attahiru, Yushau Dahiru, Nazifi Kabir, Samuel Jacob, Dennis Salisu and Muktari Buhari, Ezekiel Donatus and Nazifi Saidu. The command advised members of the public to guard against buying drugs from quacks hawking on the streets.  Police burst Kano drug syndicate Car snatchers, hemp dealers, robbers paraded in Abuja Police bust kidnapping syndicate, arrest scores, recover weapons Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin